  "prompt": "What trivia (and/or little-known facts) do you find interesting about Venezuela?",
  "response": "Here are some interesting trivia and lesser-known facts about Venezuela:\n\n1. Venezuela has the world's largest proven oil reserves and was once the wealthiest country in Latin America.\n\n2. Angel Falls, located in Venezuela, is the world's highest uninterrupted waterfall, dropping 3,212 feet (979 meters).\n\n3. Venezuela was the first country in the world to abolish the death penalty, doing so in 1863.\n\n4. The country has incredibly diverse geography, including Caribbean beaches, Andean mountains, Amazon rainforest, and desert regions.\n\n5. Venezuela has a unique geographic feature called \"Catatumbo Lightning\" where lightning storms occur almost continuously for up to 260 nights per year in one specific region.\n\n6. Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar, who liberated several South American countries from Spanish colonial rule, was Venezuelan.\n\n7. Venezuelan beauty queens have won Miss Universe more times than any other country (seven times).\n\n8. The country introduced the world's first mobile banking system in the 1990s.\n\n9. Venezuela has some of the cheapest gasoline prices globally due to heavy government subsidies.\n\n10. Despite its economic challenges, Venezuela has a very high literacy rate of around 96%.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
